Flying into Kathmandu is a thrill! The airport is surrounded by terrain and high mountains. The approach is steep, with fast changing weather into play. It is captain’s landing only. Watch how @gonationalair B747 cargo plane land there to bringing in medical aid supplies.

External footage by @flight_101_ @ktmspotter

.
.

node.text:
Watch this spectacular flypass to celebrate @qantas 100th birthday! 
Sydney has commemorated Qantas 100-year anniversary by lighting up its iconic Sydney Harbour Bridge as a larger-than-life birthday cake complete with illuminated candles that were blown out by a Qantas 787 as it did a low level overfly at 1,500 feet.

More than 1,300 LED tubes, 126 LED fixtures and 38 searchlights lit up the full expanse of the world’s most famous bridge in the ultimate tribute from Sydney, the city which has been home to Qantas for more than eight decades.
 
200 passengers, including 100 Qantas staff, were on board the 100-minute flight which was a special Centenary Scenic Flight to mark the airline’s 100th year. ✈️ (Footage: Qantas)
.
.

node.text:
Weekend vlog is out! I was in Turkey last week to fly inside an Antonov An-32P "Fire Killer". The pilot and crew demonstrated how aerial firefighting works.

The Antonov An-32P has 2 large and powerful Ivchenko AI-20DM turboprop engines and can hold 8,000 Liters of water in 2 external tanks. The pilot releases the water just 40 meters over the target. It was a precision operation to release the water. The An-32 did some excellent maneuvering during the flight. Watch all the actions in the new vlog! ✈️

#samchui #samchuiphotos #An32 #antonov32 #firefighting #aerialfirefighting #avgeek #aviationlovers #vlog #youtube

node.text:
Today marks the 20th anniversary since the demise of Ansett Australia (Mark 1). I have a story to tell.

At that time I was a university student in Australia (UNSW), I saved up a lot for a trip to Europe for planespotting. I didn’t have money to fly Business Class of course. I went for one of the cheapest but longest routing so I can maximize my trip!

My ticket was issued by ANA from Sydney via Kansai and Tokyo Narita to London. ANA code share with Ansett then and didn’t fly their own to Sydney. Just a few days before my trip on Sept 13th, Ansett Australia halted all operation. My first leg was supposedly on Ansett to Kansai. My big trip to Europe was almost cancelled. 

Luckily, ANA re-accommodated me on JAL (B747-300 Reso’cha) via Kansai and then ANA to London from Narita.

Although I didn’t fly with Ansett 747 on that trip. I was lucky enough to have flown Ansett Australia over 8 times on their spaceship B747-300 and B747-400 regularly between Sydney and Hong Kong (AN888/889)

You will always be remembered; Ansett Australia!

Weekend vlog is out! After viewing the new experimental Gulfstream G700, I was invited to a flight onboard @qatarexecutive Gulfstream G650ER.

There were a few surprises apart from the usual luxury onboard a private jet. The G650ER cabin was much quieter than any commercial airliner. The pilot drew the letter "QE" in the sky over Doha at 15,000 ft.

After lunch, the G650ER climbed to 50,000 ft which is a higher cruising altitude than all of the commercial airliners. It was a personal high for me! (On subsonic)
